1 finding that the extension is in the child's best interest.
2 (6) If custody is granted to a grandparent of the child pursuant to this section, the court
3 shall consider granting reasonable visitation rights to any other grandparent of the
4 child if the court determines visitation with the grandparent is in the best interests
5 of[has a significant and viable relationship with] the child as established in KRS
6 405.021[(1)(c)].
